OL,3,C'Resurfacing blitz' to tackle potholes
OL,4,Cwith roads to be closed for a week
OL,6,FA council says it's planning a
OL,7,F'resurfacing blitz' to tackle potholes
OL,8,Fon roads in the city.
OL,10,F47 roads, an area of 100,000 square
OL,11,Fmetres, will be treated between June
OL,12,Fand the end of July with material
OL,13,Fcalled 'microasphalt' being laid.
OL,15,FThe work is designed to make the
OL,16,Fsurface smoother, watertight and skid
OL,17,Fresist, extending the life of the road
OL,18,Fby around 10 years.
OL,20,FEach road in Brighton and Hove will be
OL,21,Fclosed for around a week.
