OL,3,C'Resurfacing blitz' to tackle potholes
OL,4,Cwith roads to be closed for a week
OL,6,FPotholes have been an increasing
OL,7,Fconcern and frustration for drivers
OL,8,Fwith mechanics seeing record numbers
OL,9,Fof repairs.
OL,11,FIn 2023, research showed cracked and
OL,12,Fgaping roads costs vehicle owners an
OL,13,Faverage of #470.
OL,15,FBerkshire based motoring group, the
OL,16,FAA, revealed at the start of the year
OL,17,Fthat it dealt with 631,852 pothole
OL,18,Frelated incidents in the year before,
OL,19,Fthe highest for five years.
